What shipped (all V1-V4 acceptance criteria in TOMOS-AIOS-PLAN.md):

V1 - In-window navigation + persistence (Tom's main complaint)
  * V1a Work window drills the case detail INSIDE the window (was a full-page jump to
    /case/<slug>/), with a working Back. Verified: open Work -> click a case -> detail
    renders in-window -> Back -> list (tests L1-L8).
  * V1b Single-source: the in-window case detail reuses the SAME i18n card keys (01-07)
    plus a shared EXTRA_CASES array (08-09, deduped out of CaseStudies.astro). The rich
    standalone write-up stays in public/case/<slug>/ and opens in a NEW TAB (target=_blank),
    so the OS is never navigated away.
  * V1c Global persistence: a canvas-scoped click interceptor in tomos.js stops any
    same-origin same-tab in-window link from doing a full-page nav; it routes /case,
    /projects, /notes links (locale-aware) to the right window + child view via
    data-os-slug, opens non-routable internal links in a new tab, and leaves
    target=_blank / mailto: / external links to open normally. Verified: no in-window
    link changes location at 1440px (tests M1-M2).
  * V1d/V1e Projects + Notes drill fully in-window; detail "open" links open a new tab;
    child-view width/wrap constrained so prose no longer overflows the window column.

V2 - Typography / layout
  * V2a All window prose forced left-aligned (neutralizes build-justify + html.kp inside
    .os-win-body); the runtime justifier opts out automatically (test N).
  * V2b Now window restyled to the About window's clean single-column rhythm (the 2-col
